11th hour saved Annie from the urgent list in San Antonio.  Poor Annie was found as a stray.  Her paperwork says that she was found hiding under a house.  After getting her to her foster home, it quickly became apparent that Annie has never had much love or affection in her life.  She is very very shy, but also very sweet, with a perpetual sad look on her little face.  Over time, she has slowly begun to open up and realize that life\'92s not so bad after all.  She loves to eat and get treats and has discovered that it\'92s pretty cool to hang out at the river with her foster sister.  We think Annie should go to a home with another calm and happy dog that can continue to let her gain confidence and show her how to be a dog again.  \
